Git submodules:
Allows for nesting referenced repositories within other repositories.

Creating submodules:
$ cd /path/to/parent-repo
$ git submodule add <git path>
$ git commit -m "Add: Submodule" 

Updating submodules:
Commits can be made to submodules just as though you are working in the original repository. It requires a commit with the submodule dir.
